title: 820-2838 - No PP3v3_S3.
message:
Customer claims "it just stopped working"; I know Duke always says 'it didn't just stop working!!" but this board is really clean with nice shiny TP all over the place.

Green / Orange light as expected.

U7201::2 == 0v. So no PP5V_S3_REG.

I get no PP3v3_S3, looking around Q7910 and Pins 1,2, 5,& 6 are 0v and pins 3 & 4 are 3.3v.
I think Q7903 is not getting P3v3S3_EN, but this won't trigger without PP5V_S3_REG right?

title: 820-2838 - No PP3v3_S3.
message: Did you short the power pads on the board? These do not auto power on!

title: 820-2838 - No PP3v3_S3.
message: Yes, shorted the pads to try turn it on.
